---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Notes" description="Public notes will be released slowly and selectively.">
	<section class="mx-auto max-w-[980px] space-y-6 pt-6">
		<div class="border-t border-black/80 pt-6">
			<p class="section-label">Notes</p>
			<h1 class="protocol-title mt-5 text-[3rem] leading-[0.92] sm:text-[5rem]">Public notes are still being prepared.</h1>
			<p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-[1.08rem] leading-8 text-ink/78">
				This section will eventually hold essays, fragments, and public working texts. It is empty on
				purpose for now. Internal memos and revision notes are not being mistaken for finished public
				writing.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="border-t border-black/35 pt-6">
			<p class="section-label">Planned forms</p>
			<div class="mt-5 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
				<div class="surface-inset px-0 py-5">
					<p class="protocol-title text-2xl">Essay</p>
					<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-ink/72">Longer public reflections once they hold their own shape.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="surface-inset px-0 py-5">
					<p class="protocol-title text-2xl">Fragment</p>
					<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-ink/72">Shorter observations that survive reduction without turning into slogans.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="surface-inset px-0 py-5">
					<p class="protocol-title text-2xl">Journal</p>
					<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-ink/72">Occasional field notes when process itself becomes worth showing.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
